column1: 23088497_17,s0,T3,T8,"To analyze the generated GFP-WIPI-1 mutants in their ability to bind PtdIns(3)P and PtdIns(3,5)P2, we first confirmed that over-expressed wild-type GFP-WIPI-1 in different cell lines that either express detectable (G361) or undetectable (HeLa, U2OS) levels of endogenous ",WIPI-1," protein (Figure 6A), predominantly binds ",PtdIns(3)P," and to a minor extend PtdIns(3,5)P2 (Figure 6B and 6C upper panel).
